<seg id=1> Chinese Company Now Largest Investor In Macau </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Macau, April 3 (Wang Zhigen and Dong Yuming reporting): Zhang Xuming, president of the Macau-China Enterprise Association, said that there are currently two hundred Chinese-invested enterprises in Macau with assets valued at more than 90 billion Macau patacas. </seg>
<seg id=3> Macau's largest investors are now Chinese. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> At the recent meeting marking the fifth anniversary of the Macau-China Enterprise Association, Zhang Xuming said that Macau enterprises investing in China's interior range from small to large and weak to strong, and have become an important force in Macau's development. </seg>
<seg id=5> They have made an important contribution to the steady prosperity of Macau. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> According to reports, these companies are involved in a broad range of business activities, including trade, industry, finance, insurance, tourism, food and drink, transportation and real estate. </seg>
<seg id=7> Chinese investment accounts for 50 percent of the finance and insurance industries there, from 50 to 70 percent of the tourism industry, imports-exports 30 percent, and for real estate 70 percent. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Zhang Xuming said that Macau's Chinese-invested enterprises will continue to be guided by both Deng Xiaoping's concept of "one country, two systems" and  China's policies toward Hong Kong and Macau. The principle of "doing what you can do, not what you can't" will be insisted upon, along with working hard with the locals in the business community, making for an even larger contribution both to the stability of Macau's economy and the development of its society. </seg>
</p>
